*** Start Node server:
- run command below:
  1.  >node server.js
  2. or >npm run server

*** Start client app:
 - cd to client folder and run below command:
  >npm start

*** Install Sequelize to working with PostgreSQL DB:
>npm install -g sequelize-cli

===========================================
Database setup & configuration
Ref link: https://scotch.io/tutorials/getting-started-with-node-express-and-postgres-using-sequelize
===========================================
*** Configure Sequelize for our project(file .sequelizerc in root folder)

*** Install packages
>npm install --save sequelize pg pg-hstore
>sequelize init
>createdb todos-dev [optional]

*** Generating models;
>sequelize model:create --name Category --attributes name:string



*** Run migrate scripts:
>sequelize db:migrate
